reviews.text: Good pizza place.  It is only take out so no eating there.  The crust was not crisp on the Mr. Jim's special.  I like a crispy crust on the bottom. The brownie bites were a bit dry but good. Reasonable prices and they gave a military discount.  I would go back.

Super disappointed, a friend highly recommended this place. Pizza and breadsticks have zero flavor. Sauce has no flavor. Its was delivered really fast. But was not what I expected.  This was 32 dollars for a medium. My husband didn't like it either. üòï

Would like to preface that I have worked in restaurants for 15 years and rarely, if ever, leave reviews, and am not seeking any sort of recompense from visit to this place today.

I legitimately do not understand any of the positive reviews for this place.

This was my first ever experience going to Mr. Jim's, and will be my last. The "extra large" pizza is smaller than anywhere else. The pizza had very little sauce, was given to me cold, and the dough is clearly not made fresh at all. Frozen pizzas from a grocery store are of better quality than this place.

Save your money and avoid this place. I wish I did, I would've saved $36!
We always get good pizza here.  They are always busy.  Only complaint/warning is to check before you take it out.  They sometimes get my order wrong.  Overall good food.

Chain pizza place with reliably decent chain style pizza. No dining room. Priced a little high for what you get, but appropriate for the area and there are budget type options.
My first trip here was based off a recommendation that didn‚Äôt include the information that there is no dining room. I got my order relatively quick and there is a comfortable(ish) place to wait. The staff was extremely pleasant and deserves 5/5. Unfortunately the staff experience, to me, isn‚Äôt worth the drive for mediocre pizza.

editorial_summary.overview: Counter-serve chain offering pizza with lots of toppings in original or thinner-crust versions.

detailedReviews.author: David T (David T)
detailedReviews.text: Based on my recent experience with Mr. Jim‚Äôs Pizza, I wasn‚Äôt seeking a free replacement pizza, which was offered. I simply wanted to share my feedback with the owner. Unfortunately, he seemed uninterested in discussing his business. The pizza was so bad that even for free, it wasn‚Äôt worth it. It lacked flavor, suggesting a decline in quality standards. The toppings were sparse, with almost no cheese or sauce. Additionally, the store was noticeably dirty, reflecting poorly on the management. Having enjoyed Mr. Jim‚Äôs pizzas for many years in Texas, this visit in Las Vegas was a huge disappointment and will be my last.

detailedReviews.text: I‚Äôve been eating Mr. Jim‚Äôs for 4 years. Today was the first time they ever messed up my order. I didn‚Äôt really think much of it just filled out the survey which I rarely do and mentioned the messed up items. The store manager called me and asked how to make it right! Which they did and I didn‚Äôt expect. I‚Äôll likely be a customer here as long as I live in the area. Top notch. I should mention I love their pizza as well. Good ingredients and a tasty crust! Very reasonably priced as well.

detailedReviews.author: Michael Butcher
detailedReviews.text: Bought 2 large pizzas and a small Jim stix.I feel that the pizza was a bit overpriced considering that it lacked flavors that warranted $65. I would really like to see seasoning make its way to one of these pies. I mean honestly you could buy pizza from Costco and get a better quality food for cheaper! I mean if you are not going to be about quality then please quit price gouging customers. If you are going to be about quality then quit using cheap ingredients. For the price charged that should have been the best pizza I ever ate! I also want to talk about on atmosphere and feel that your restaurant is rather uninspiring and seems to lack any kind of identity. What differentiates you from any other small pizza hole in the wall? Nothing, in my opinion. Oh and none of your employees look like they want to be there. They don‚Äôt say it but they don‚Äôt look interested in helping anyone.

detailedReviews.text: Just my personal preference, ask or comment with your order to cook your pizza well done. If not it is very limp/soggy.

detailedReviews.text: NOT WORTH IT! Terrible. This pizza was the most disgusting pizza our family has ever had, we could not even eat it. I made something different. It was made of rubber, super chewy, no flavor, hardly any toppings, hard to tear apart, I mean, we've gotten better pizza from the frozen section.  They say, you get what you pay for but in this case, the quality does NOT match the price. I normally don't leave reviews but it was THAT BAD!

I was just shocked about this. I hope they since removed these items from their front freezer

That is going straight into the companies pocket for sending a driver right down the street. So sad, this place used to be great.

I used to be a customer. Then their food started lacking. Now it is even worse.

The pizza had next to no toppings and was almost raw! I called them to kindly alert them to how bad the pizza was. They made no attempt to make anything right. The lady who took my order didn't even apologize for the obvious lack of following instructions. Well-done does not mean raw. I paid for extra toppings and got almost nothing! Order elsewhere!

detailedReviews.text: We tried this pizza last night for the first time. It‚Äôs wonderful, & it‚Äôs family owned as well. Two brothers & their sister work there & were so friendly & personable. Double Pepperoni with regular crust is a straight 10/10. The cheese crust is unfortunately alert down and the reason I took a star off. It's basically a quesadilla under your pizza. Response: it's just melted but 'uncooked' cheese. Maybe need to melt the cheese on a griddle or skillet and then transfer it to the cheese crust?

detailedReviews.author: Bazooka Joe
detailedReviews.text: Good Pizza, Good Prices. I love their chewy dough and they were not afraid to be generous with the toppings. The staff is consistently friendly and responsive, with management taking proactive steps to resolve any issues, enhancing customer loyalty. - review management can highlight this positive aspect
improvementOpportunities: Negative reviews and reputation issues related to poor food quality and customer service - review management can address this concern
